BS, XI, 651-53 (J.-M. Sauget) .
Sauget , "Fragment" ' 225-28, propose !'identification de Sarbil a THUTHAEL (q.v.) et
a EUTAL (q.v.).</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-1454">Sharbel and his sister Babai were martyrs
            of <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/78">Edessa</placeName>. Sharbel had been a
          pagan priest, but he converted to Christianity. He was martyred under Trajan. Sharbel and
          Babai were contemporary with the priest <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1162">Barsamya</persName>.</note>
